description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated and enthusiastic person to work in the Estates department at Royal Lancaster Infirmary. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should be experienced, time served and suitably qualified in mechanical engineering/ fitting maintenance, fault finding, and repairs. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should also be proficient in small scale installation work on mechanical services, plant and equipment at the Hospital and other local health care premises. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Flexible working will be required where you will assist other trades and undertake other tasks to maintain the building services. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLuke OldlandJob titleEngineering ManagerEmail addressluke.oldland@mbht.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Luke Oldland - luke.oldland@mbht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
